<blockquote>
<p>Markdown parser done right. Fast and easy to extend.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong><a href="https://markdown-it.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Live demo<ExternalLinkIcon/></a></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Follows the <strong><a href="http://spec.commonmark.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CommonMark spec<ExternalLinkIcon/></a></strong> + adds syntax extensions &amp; sugar (URL autolinking, typographer).</li>
<li>Configurable syntax! You can add new rules and even replace existing ones.</li>
<li>High speed.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/markdown-it/markdown-it/tree/master/docs/security.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Safe<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> by default.</li>
<li>Community-written <strong><a href="https://www.npmjs.org/browse/keyword/markdown-it-plugin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">plugins<ExternalLinkIcon/></a></strong> and <a href="https://www.npmjs.org/browse/keyword/markdown-it" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">other packages<ExternalLinkIcon/></a> on npm.</li>
</ul>
